      "body": "One area to explore for a possible solution to this is to use a unit test instead of a functional test. The reason being that in the unit test we have greater control of the internals of the program. This would allow us to create a `CConnman` object with mocked `interruptNet` member which sleeps less than requested and call its `ThreadOpenAddedConnections()` method. This would also be useful in fuzz tests like https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/28584 where the sleep is only slowing down the execution.",
